				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Melanie's Melifluous Motion and Doors<a name="19199"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 5 04 1:52 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Back to the uses of this song.  The primary use for this song is avoidance.  If a mob roots most of your group down you can use this song to keep them moving to avoid getting hit.  Another use is in an emergency when you need to put a little distance between your group and the mob so you can run to a zone.
<br />
However, I have only ever had this song up for novelty purposes.  During most battles I have not found it to be a song needed for much of anything.  I believe that this song was given to us for pure PvP purposes so that a rooted bard might have a chance to escape some damage.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=641487">Ellorra Dannen</a><br>
Bard of the 65th Song<br><br>

Myrrialle Thuleanna<br>
Druid of the 55th Ring<br>

Innoruuk Server</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
